WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.541
Wouldn't you rather give it all at once
to something real?

2
00:00:09.291 --> 00:00:11.041
What would we be stealing?

3
00:00:11.125 --> 00:00:14.476
The quarterly payroll
for an entire Imperial sector.

4
00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.601
Blevin. this incident on Ferrix.

5
00:00:16.625 --> 00:00:19.309
Corporate Security. sir.
They're still in charge out there.

6
00:00:19.333 --> 00:00:22.476
A stolen Imperial Star path unit
was recovered at the scene.

7
00:00:22.500 --> 00:00:23.559
<i>Five months in?</i>

8
00:00:23.583 --> 00:00:26.101
Just plug in some new person?
It'll tear the team apart.

9
00:00:26.125 --> 00:00:27.851
I'm buying you critical redundancy.

10
00:00:27.875 --> 00:00:29.916
- What do you mean "buying"?
- I'm paying him.

11
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.059
We've been eating roots
and sleeping on rocks for this rebellion

12
00:00:33.083 --> 00:00:35.041
and now you've got a mercenary on board?

13
00:00:35.125 --> 00:00:37.226
<i>Take him or call it off.</i>

14
00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:40.291
- You're taking on an Imperial armory?
- Are you not joining us?

15
00:00:40.375 --> 00:00:42.309
<i>Us? How many of us are there?</i>

16
00:00:42.333 --> 00:00:43.434
<i>Now we are seven.</i>

17
00:00:43.458 --> 00:00:44.934
That's Skeen.

18
00:00:44.958 --> 00:00:46.309
Taramyn.

19
00:00:46.333 --> 00:00:47.416
Nemik.

20
00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:49.476
- Cinta. And Lieutenant Gorn.
- Who is he?

21
00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:51.476
He's Clem.
He's here. That's all that matters.

22
00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:53.541
We're wasting daylight.
Let's get on with it.

23
00:00:53.625 --> 00:00:59.541
As of this morning. the Morlana system
is under permanent Imperial authority.

24
00:00:59.625 --> 00:01:01.041
<i>Congratulations on that.</i>

25
00:01:01.625 --> 00:01:02.833
Mother.

26
00:01:03.708 --> 00:01:04.916
Senator.

27
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:07.791
- If you can't deliver. I need to know.
- The money's there.

28
00:01:07.875 --> 00:01:10.059
It's just getting very dangerous
to move it around.

29
00:01:10.083 --> 00:01:11.976
You think I haven't thought this through?

30
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:13.851
I'd be the first one to fall.

31
00:01:13.875 --> 00:01:15.083
That's a vault.

32
00:01:15.666 --> 00:01:17.916
We're taking crates of payroll
from that room.

33
00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:20.851
loading the freighter.
and escaping out of the runway tunnel.

34
00:01:20.875 --> 00:01:24.416
What we need to know is.
are you in all the way?

35
00:01:25.583 --> 00:01:26.958
Let's get to it.

36
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:34.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

37
00:02:52.375 --> 00:02:53.375
Syril.

38
00:02:54.333 --> 00:02:55.791
You're slouching.

39
00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:05.416
Is that how you've been
presenting yourself to the world?

40
00:03:06.583 --> 00:03:08.166
It would explain a great deal.

41
00:03:11.791 --> 00:03:16.541
Being a leader
isn't something one just turns on and off.

42
00:03:18.958 --> 00:03:22.416
By the time you've remembered
to sit up straight. it's too late.

43
00:03:24.083 --> 00:03:29.041
You might as well wear a sign that says.
"I promise to disappoint you."

44
00:03:30.875 --> 00:03:34.184
Shame we couldn't have seen more
of each other when you were flourishing.

45
00:03:34.208 --> 00:03:36.166
I'd have the memory to sustain me.

46
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.416
Well. you could've come
any time you wanted.

47
00:03:39.500 --> 00:03:44.351
Any civilized being knows an open
invitation is no invitation at all.

48
00:03:44.375 --> 00:03:48.434
My assumption is.
you have no prospect for the future.

49
00:03:48.458 --> 00:03:49.625
I had a spare room.

50
00:03:51.250 --> 00:03:52.934
Could've visited any time you wanted.

51
00:03:52.958 --> 00:03:55.059
- You know that.
- I know what you tell me.

52
00:03:55.083 --> 00:03:56.351
I intuit the rest.

53
00:03:56.375 --> 00:04:00.208
I intuit you have no future prospects.

54
00:04:00.833 --> 00:04:03.250
I'd forgotten the precision
of your predictive powers.

55
00:04:04.208 --> 00:04:07.541
- Ah. you've remembered how to mock me.
- Forgotten how sensitive you can be.

56
00:04:07.625 --> 00:04:09.184
Perhaps you've forgotten my question.

57
00:04:09.208 --> 00:04:12.791
Do you have even
a single prospect before you?

58
00:04:14.541 --> 00:04:15.625
I'll find a way.

59
00:04:18.208 --> 00:04:19.541
I'm calling Uncle Harlo.

60
00:04:19.666 --> 00:04:21.851
I'm calling in the family favor.

61
00:04:21.875 --> 00:04:23.434
Haven't heard that in a while.

62
00:04:23.458 --> 00:04:24.791
These are desperate times.

63
00:04:24.875 --> 00:04:27.541
- You're assuming he'll remember you.
- That's amusing.

64
00:04:27.625 --> 00:04:29.226
And you think he'll talk to you?

65
00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:30.351
I know he will.

66
00:04:30.375 --> 00:04:32.101
And he'll know why I called.

67
00:04:32.125 --> 00:04:34.916
And he'll respect me
for having waited so long in asking

68
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:37.291
and being so prudent about my request.

69
00:04:37.375 --> 00:04:39.958
What is it you'll be asking for?

70
00:04:40.958 --> 00:04:43.601
Someone who will take you on. Syril.

71
00:04:43.625 --> 00:04:45.375
Setting the bar high. are we?

72
00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.333
Uncle Harlo will know what's best.

73
00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:35.625
It's all there.

74
00:05:36.708 --> 00:05:38.250
Vel asked me to have a look.

75
00:05:39.583 --> 00:05:42.500
I think
she's having second thoughts.

76
00:05:44.625 --> 00:05:46.059
Go talk to her if you want.

77
00:05:46.083 --> 00:05:47.208
She'll be up soon.

78
00:05:50.833 --> 00:05:52.166
You didn't come with much.

79
00:05:53.458 --> 00:05:54.684
That plus the bad arm?

80
00:05:54.708 --> 00:05:57.250
It's pretty clear
you left wherever you were in a hurry.

81
00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.458
Corporate issue. Interesting.

82
00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:06.208
There's no sense bein' upset.

83
00:06:07.458 --> 00:06:09.208
You're lucky to be alive right now.

84
00:06:10.541 --> 00:06:13.291
We've been down here for months.
and the stakes are high.

85
00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:16.351
- How's your arm?
- I'll be fine.

86
00:06:16.375 --> 00:06:17.500
Uh-huh.

87
00:06:18.375 --> 00:06:20.708
And. uh. who... whose is this?

88
00:06:22.166 --> 00:06:23.208
Didn't get a name.

89
00:06:30.791 --> 00:06:31.791
Oh.

90
00:06:32.833 --> 00:06:34.666
You know what this means. don't you?

91
00:06:36.166 --> 00:06:38.083
Yeah. I saw your eyes go right to it.

92
00:06:39.083 --> 00:06:40.125
Krayt Head.

93
00:06:41.375 --> 00:06:42.708
See. they don't know.

94
00:06:44.416 --> 00:06:45.541
They got no idea.

95
00:06:47.750 --> 00:06:48.875
What about this?

96
00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:52.041
"By The Hand."

97
00:06:53.583 --> 00:06:54.666
So. where were you?

98
00:06:56.125 --> 00:06:57.351
Sipo.

99
00:06:57.375 --> 00:06:58.541
Youth center.

100
00:06:59.708 --> 00:07:01.833
Three years. I was 13 when I went in.

101
00:07:03.625 --> 00:07:04.750
I never heard of it.

102
00:07:06.083 --> 00:07:08.541
- Well. you didn't miss anything.
- Yeah.

103
00:07:09.625 --> 00:07:11.500
They've built a lot of cages. huh?

104
00:07:12.166 --> 00:07:14.416
"The axe forgets. but the tree remembers."

105
00:07:16.666 --> 00:07:18.500
Now it's our turn to do the chopping.

106
00:07:20.541 --> 00:07:21.601
So. that's it?

107
00:07:21.625 --> 00:07:23.041
That's why you're here?

108
00:07:23.125 --> 00:07:24.125
Revenge?

109
00:07:25.291 --> 00:07:26.833
Yeah. that's good enough for now.

110
00:07:28.416 --> 00:07:29.416
You?

111
00:07:32.666 --> 00:07:34.541
I was told I could help.

112
00:07:35.208 --> 00:07:37.083
Yeah. but you won't say by who.

113
00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:40.083
Working with other people is never easy.

114
00:07:40.916 --> 00:07:41.916
Yeah.

115
00:07:42.708 --> 00:07:44.958
I didn't mark you for a team player.

116
00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:48.476
It always breaks at the weakest point.

117
00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:50.083
Oh. you're worried about the kids.

118
00:07:51.666 --> 00:07:53.309
Nemik's a surprise.

119
00:07:53.333 --> 00:07:54.726
He's green. but he's all in.

120
00:07:54.750 --> 00:07:56.101
He's a true believer.

121
00:07:56.125 --> 00:07:57.583
Nothing but the cause for him.

122
00:07:59.500 --> 00:08:00.477
Then there's Cinta.

123
00:08:00.501 --> 00:08:02.000
Cinta Kaz.

124
00:08:02.708 --> 00:08:04.750
She's stone cold and fearless.

125
00:08:05.416 --> 00:08:07.083
Probably the toughest one here.

126
00:08:08.666 --> 00:08:11.875
She's already sharin' a blanket.
if that's what you're wonderin'.

127
00:08:14.125 --> 00:08:15.208
And the Lieutenant?

128
00:08:16.583 --> 00:08:18.166
Without him. there's no plan.

129
00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:20.559
He could be walking us right into a trap.

130
00:08:20.583 --> 00:08:22.750
They would've taken us down by now.

131
00:08:24.750 --> 00:08:26.500
Or maybe that's what you're here for.

132
00:08:30.250 --> 00:08:32.416
I'm here to win and walk away.

133
00:08:34.333 --> 00:08:35.666
Wouldn't that be lovely?

134
00:08:49.250 --> 00:08:50.500
The driver's here.

135
00:08:51.250 --> 00:08:52.476
Kloris.

136
00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:53.583
Yes.

137
00:08:55.458 --> 00:08:56.625
You know his name.

138
00:08:57.625 --> 00:08:58.625
Is Leida ready?

139
00:09:00.166 --> 00:09:01.166
I'm not sure.

140
00:09:01.791 --> 00:09:03.708
Where is she? Leida?

141
00:09:07.708 --> 00:09:09.309
Hmm. Did you eat?

142
00:09:09.333 --> 00:09:10.726
When would that have happened?

143
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:11.851
I just came down.

144
00:09:11.875 --> 00:09:13.226
Take something for the ride.

145
00:09:13.250 --> 00:09:14.958
- What?
- We need to be going.

146
00:09:15.500 --> 00:09:16.916
Oh. Change in plan.

147
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:18.000
Dad's taking me.

148
00:09:18.458 --> 00:09:19.750
You're taking me. right?

149
00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:22.083
Got to clear it with her.

150
00:09:24.416 --> 00:09:26.083
I don't have early class today.

151
00:09:27.041 --> 00:09:29.125
- We planned this.
- You did.

152
00:09:29.833 --> 00:09:31.976
Get your coat. It's not up for discussion.

153
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:33.559
Are you serious?

154
00:09:33.583 --> 00:09:35.059
Am I serious?

155
00:09:35.083 --> 00:09:37.333
Just go. You're off the hook.

156
00:09:38.625 --> 00:09:39.958
Enjoying this?

157
00:09:41.083 --> 00:09:42.208
Get your coat.

158
00:09:42.791 --> 00:09:44.976
It's out of your way anyway.
so what's the point?

159
00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:47.476
The point is. we have a schedule.
the driver's waiting.

160
00:09:47.500 --> 00:09:50.976
- I've planned on this. and we're going.
- You're only doing it to show off.

161
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:52.500
- What?
- Just go.

162
00:09:53.625 --> 00:09:55.226
What would I be showing off?

163
00:09:55.250 --> 00:09:57.166
That you're involved somehow.

164
00:09:59.458 --> 00:10:00.916
What? That's just...

165
00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:03.000
Nobody cares. You can relax.

166
00:10:04.458 --> 00:10:06.541
That's just so hurtful.

167
00:10:07.375 --> 00:10:09.541
- See? There you go.
- Go where?

168
00:10:09.625 --> 00:10:10.791
That's my point.

169
00:10:11.666 --> 00:10:13.291
It's all about you. isn't it?

170
00:10:13.375 --> 00:10:14.434
It's always all about you.

171
00:10:14.458 --> 00:10:16.476
Is this really
how you'd like to start the day?

172
00:10:16.500 --> 00:10:18.125
I didn't choose this conversation.

173
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:26.625
I so appreciate the support.

174
00:10:47.708 --> 00:10:48.708
Dray milk.

175
00:10:51.541 --> 00:10:52.684
You can live on it.

176
00:10:52.708 --> 00:10:55.708
You may question your existence
after a few days. but...

177
00:10:58.958 --> 00:11:00.375
Memorable. isn't it?

178
00:11:07.125 --> 00:11:08.416
That's an old one.

179
00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:09.934
Old and true.

180
00:11:09.958 --> 00:11:11.041
And sturdy.

181
00:11:11.125 --> 00:11:13.458
One of the best
navigational tools ever built.

182
00:11:13.958 --> 00:11:15.309
Can't be jammed or intercepted.

183
00:11:15.333 --> 00:11:17.500
Something breaks. you can fix it yourself.

184
00:11:18.333 --> 00:11:19.666
Hard to learn.

185
00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:23.125
Yes. but once you've mastered it.
you're free.

186
00:11:23.833 --> 00:11:26.976
We've grown reliant on Imperial tech.
and we've made ourselves vulnerable.

187
00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.226
There's a growing list
of things we've known and forgotten.

188
00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:30.559
things they've pushed us to forget.

189
00:11:30.583 --> 00:11:32.375
Things like freedom.

190
00:11:33.541 --> 00:11:35.333
Nemik sees oppression everywhere.

191
00:11:35.958 --> 00:11:39.250
Skeen pretends not to listen.
but I know the message is sinking in.

192
00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:42.434
He's writin' a manifesto.

193
00:11:42.458 --> 00:11:43.541
Did he tell you?

194
00:11:44.166 --> 00:11:47.351
Apparently. the only thing keepin' us
from liberty is a few more ideas.

195
00:11:47.375 --> 00:11:48.541
Few more ideas.

196
00:11:48.625 --> 00:11:49.934
It's so confusing. isn't it?

197
00:11:49.958 --> 00:11:53.351
So much going wrong. so much to say.
and all of it happening so quickly.

198
00:11:53.375 --> 00:11:56.184
The pace of repression
outstrips our ability to understand it.

199
00:11:56.208 --> 00:11:58.434
And that is the real trick
of the Imperial thought machine.

200
00:11:58.458 --> 00:12:01.916
It's easier to hide behind
40 atrocities than a single incident.

201
00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.101
But they have a fight on their hands.
don't they?

202
00:12:04.125 --> 00:12:06.791
Our elemental rights
are such a simple thing to hold.

203
00:12:06.875 --> 00:12:09.434
they will have to shake the galaxy hard
to loosen our grip.

204
00:12:09.458 --> 00:12:11.208
I'd like to hear what Clem believes.

205
00:12:14.291 --> 00:12:15.666
I know what I'm against.

206
00:12:16.791 --> 00:12:18.434
Everything else will have to wait.

207
00:12:18.458 --> 00:12:20.351
You're my ideal reader.

208
00:12:20.375 --> 00:12:23.351
- Now you've done it.
- Haven't titled it yet. I've been waiting.

209
00:12:23.375 --> 00:12:26.351
It's a work in progress. and I know
that there's a great deal left to say.

210
00:12:26.375 --> 00:12:27.726
I mean. look.

211
00:12:27.750 --> 00:12:28.833
Right here.

212
00:12:29.375 --> 00:12:30.352
Fresh inspiration.

213
00:12:30.376 --> 00:12:33.041
Two seemingly random objects.
and yet this charts an astral path.

214
00:12:33.125 --> 00:12:35.226
this maps the trail
of political consciousness.

215
00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:36.351
Both systems based on truth.

216
00:12:36.375 --> 00:12:38.559
both navigating toward clear
and achievable outcomes.

217
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:40.166
- Basic facts expanded to...
- Clem.

218
00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:43.500
To be continued.

219
00:12:45.708 --> 00:12:47.625
Busy day. Clem. Finish your milk.

220
00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.125
You don't trust him?

221
00:13:03.416 --> 00:13:04.583
- I barely trust you.
- Hmm.

222
00:13:05.166 --> 00:13:07.291
Obviously. it's a track launch.

223
00:13:07.375 --> 00:13:10.184
so there's an adjusted thrust ratio
to make it up the ramp.

224
00:13:10.208 --> 00:13:12.250
- Okay.
- It's on an overhead rail.

225
00:13:13.833 --> 00:13:16.166
- Has to be. yeah.
- So calibrating the weight...

226
00:13:18.625 --> 00:13:20.559
- What about it?
- How would you do it?

227
00:13:20.583 --> 00:13:22.291
How would I know the weight?

228
00:13:23.583 --> 00:13:24.833
Is this a test?

229
00:13:25.708 --> 00:13:26.791
It's a simple question.

230
00:13:29.208 --> 00:13:31.559
You don't know
how to get it off the runway. do you?

231
00:13:31.583 --> 00:13:32.851
We know how to fly it.

232
00:13:32.875 --> 00:13:34.916
Yeah. but you've
got to get it up there first.

233
00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:36.458
Answer the question.

234
00:13:36.875 --> 00:13:38.333
You really don't.

235
00:13:39.291 --> 00:13:40.333
Do you?

236
00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:42.476
You don't know how to get it out of there.

237
00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:44.458
How do you input the weight?

238
00:13:45.708 --> 00:13:47.916
- You sure it's on the rail?
- Yes.

239
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:49.601
It's mounted?

240
00:13:49.625 --> 00:13:50.934
It's ready to go?

241
00:13:50.958 --> 00:13:52.684
That's how they keep it.
you're sure of that?

242
00:13:52.708 --> 00:13:54.000
Yes. we're sure.

243
00:13:54.583 --> 00:13:57.666
Lieutenant Gorn is in there every day.

244
00:13:58.333 --> 00:13:59.310
Okay.

245
00:13:59.334 --> 00:14:00.934
There's a load clutch.

246
00:14:00.958 --> 00:14:04.916
It... It's a big ugly handle
just right next to the booster throttle.

247
00:14:05.625 --> 00:14:09.851
There's a gauge just below
to read out the weight.

248
00:14:09.875 --> 00:14:11.601
Why isn't this in the manual?

249
00:14:11.625 --> 00:14:13.791
Because it's a custom job.

250
00:14:13.875 --> 00:14:15.458
It's an add-on.

251
00:14:15.583 --> 00:14:18.458
What were you gonna do
if I wasn't here?

252
00:14:18.583 --> 00:14:21.309
Might have been ugly
but we'd have figured it out.

253
00:14:21.333 --> 00:14:23.083
We wanted to be sure.

254
00:14:23.250 --> 00:14:26.559
- Oh. Okay. I'll pilot.
- No. you'll do as you're told.

255
00:14:26.583 --> 00:14:27.726
Ah. I'm flying it.

256
00:14:27.750 --> 00:14:29.559
We can say it's your idea. I don't care.

257
00:14:29.583 --> 00:14:33.125
But if it's my ass on the line.
I'm pulling this thing out of there.

258
00:14:37.166 --> 00:14:38.750
- Okay.
- Okay.

259
00:14:55.833 --> 00:14:57.041
Clem.

260
00:15:02.250 --> 00:15:03.250
The tower yard.

261
00:15:04.416 --> 00:15:05.416
The dam.

262
00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:08.958
The garrison HQ
and the barracks up top by the east end.

263
00:15:10.041 --> 00:15:11.125
The Rono tunnel.

264
00:15:12.250 --> 00:15:13.708
The flight control tower.

265
00:15:14.458 --> 00:15:18.208
And objective number one.
the door at the base of the tower.

266
00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:22.125
The Temple Path.

267
00:15:23.166 --> 00:15:27.333
Now. the real thing has a downhill pitch.
but the distance is right.

268
00:15:28.500 --> 00:15:31.000
And down there.
where we'll be coming from.

269
00:15:32.041 --> 00:15:33.041
The Old Temple.

270
00:15:36.208 --> 00:15:37.208
Got it.

271
00:15:44.458 --> 00:15:45.541
What's this?

272
00:15:49.333 --> 00:15:50.333
Target practice?

273
00:15:53.250 --> 00:15:54.333
Where are they?

274
00:15:57.375 --> 00:15:58.916
This was to be cleaned up yesterday.

275
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:01.041
- Where are they?
- They should be back soon. sir.

276
00:16:01.125 --> 00:16:02.416
Back from where?

277
00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:04.309
I believe they're in the tower. sir.

278
00:16:04.333 --> 00:16:07.416
The Commandant's wife needed help
moving furniture for the dinner.

279
00:16:11.333 --> 00:16:12.541
I'll be back in an hour.

280
00:16:12.625 --> 00:16:15.916
This had better be well on its way.
or I promise you.

281
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:18.875
I'll be revisiting
the schedule for winter furloughs.

282
00:16:25.958 --> 00:16:28.458
You are Imperial Private Clem.

283
00:16:29.041 --> 00:16:33.541
You're a sentry from the Alkenzi Airbase
transferred for special duty.

284
00:16:34.833 --> 00:16:35.833
Shoulders back.

285
00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:38.750
- More.
- Don't touch me.

286
00:16:41.833 --> 00:16:43.500
You want something. you tell me.

287
00:16:46.500 --> 00:16:47.833
Can you walk like a soldier?

288
00:16:49.750 --> 00:16:51.000
I've seen it done.

289
00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:54.184
Let's find out
if you've been payin' attention.

290
00:16:54.208 --> 00:16:55.291
Form up.

291
00:17:10.708 --> 00:17:13.101
I don't care where it goes.
Just get it out of here.

292
00:17:13.125 --> 00:17:14.625
Yes. sir. Right away. sir.

293
00:17:15.375 --> 00:17:16.666
Captain Tigo!

294
00:17:19.708 --> 00:17:20.916
There you are.

295
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:22.666
They're still clearing out some guests.

296
00:17:25.416 --> 00:17:26.684
What do you think?

297
00:17:26.708 --> 00:17:27.791
As a hotel?

298
00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:30.708
Do you want it or not?

299
00:17:31.250 --> 00:17:32.559
The assignment?

300
00:17:32.583 --> 00:17:34.434
No. you're taking the assignment.

301
00:17:34.458 --> 00:17:36.875
I was asking if this would do
as your headquarters.

302
00:17:38.791 --> 00:17:40.125
Could I be made Prefect?

303
00:17:40.958 --> 00:17:43.416
The title.
I know it doesn't come with extra pay.

304
00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:46.000
You can wear a ball gown if you'd like.

305
00:17:46.708 --> 00:17:49.500
Just get this up and running
before my next staff meeting.

306
00:17:57.625 --> 00:17:59.166
It's about confidence.

307
00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:00.684
We belong here.

308
00:18:00.708 --> 00:18:02.000
We're followin' orders.

309
00:18:02.958 --> 00:18:04.851
The door's bein' opened as we approach.

310
00:18:04.875 --> 00:18:07.726
Lieutenant Gorn will be out front.
He's the leader.

311
00:18:07.750 --> 00:18:09.041
He's the gatekeeper.

312
00:18:09.125 --> 00:18:11.541
So eyes on him at all times.

313
00:18:11.625 --> 00:18:13.541
We're locked in. We're listenin'.

314
00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:15.101
We're ready to adapt.

315
00:18:15.125 --> 00:18:18.375
And last man in bolts the door behind him.

316
00:18:19.500 --> 00:18:21.250
Squad. halt.

317
00:18:24.583 --> 00:18:25.583
Questions?

318
00:18:26.291 --> 00:18:27.666
What are they doing?

319
00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:29.851
Never mind about them.

320
00:18:29.875 --> 00:18:32.041
You got enough to worry about.

321
00:18:32.708 --> 00:18:34.083
Let's walk it again at speed.

322
00:18:35.208 --> 00:18:36.375
You should switch.

323
00:18:37.541 --> 00:18:38.541
What?

324
00:18:39.333 --> 00:18:40.625
He's left-handed.

325
00:18:41.250 --> 00:18:42.583
Should swap sides.

326
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:46.309
Why don't you get a handle
on what we're doing here

327
00:18:46.333 --> 00:18:48.291
before you start making suggestions.

328
00:18:49.916 --> 00:18:51.208
Why?

329
00:18:52.541 --> 00:18:53.583
Why switch sides?

330
00:18:55.125 --> 00:18:56.375
Skeen is left-handed.

331
00:18:57.583 --> 00:18:59.166
You want your weapon on the outside.

332
00:19:02.125 --> 00:19:04.083
- What am I?
- Right-handed.

333
00:19:04.750 --> 00:19:05.750
Taramyn?

334
00:19:06.333 --> 00:19:07.684
- Right.
- Cinta?

335
00:19:07.708 --> 00:19:08.791
Right.

336
00:19:08.875 --> 00:19:10.041
Nemik?

337
00:19:10.125 --> 00:19:12.833
Favors right. but shoots left.

338
00:19:16.500 --> 00:19:17.500
Fine.

339
00:19:18.791 --> 00:19:19.791
Let's switch.

340
00:19:22.625 --> 00:19:24.291
Any other suggestions?

341
00:19:26.250 --> 00:19:27.333
Wait!

342
00:19:31.666 --> 00:19:32.750
Cover the guns.

343
00:19:34.083 --> 00:19:35.333
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

344
00:19:42.916 --> 00:19:45.083
- He's gone.
- I don't think so.

345
00:20:10.875 --> 00:20:11.875
They'll soon see.

346
00:20:12.875 --> 00:20:15.500
Surprise from above
is never as shocking as one from below.

347
00:20:29.458 --> 00:20:30.791
Corporal Kimzi.

348
00:20:30.875 --> 00:20:31.875
Sir.

349
00:20:32.583 --> 00:20:33.560
Enjoying the view?

350
00:20:33.584 --> 00:20:34.666
Yes. sir.

351
00:20:35.708 --> 00:20:37.750
Gets a bit stale in there sometimes.

352
00:20:41.041 --> 00:20:43.166
It's always inspiring. isn't it?

353
00:20:44.666 --> 00:20:45.750
I suppose.

354
00:20:48.125 --> 00:20:50.541
Is it true they're tearing this all down?

355
00:20:51.125 --> 00:20:52.208
It's been discussed.

356
00:20:52.958 --> 00:20:54.208
Move the airbase here?

357
00:20:55.625 --> 00:20:56.666
That makes sense.

358
00:20:56.750 --> 00:20:58.184
It's a big project.

359
00:20:58.208 --> 00:21:00.958
Not too many Dhanis
to worry about anymore though. eh?

360
00:21:02.041 --> 00:21:03.875
How many do you think we'll have tomorrow?

361
00:21:04.750 --> 00:21:05.750
I don't know.

362
00:21:06.958 --> 00:21:08.583
It was less than a hundred last time.

363
00:21:09.416 --> 00:21:11.250
Still enough to smell 'em. right?

364
00:21:13.333 --> 00:21:16.083
Can you imagine this place
with a couple of thousand of them?

365
00:21:18.791 --> 00:21:19.833
Yes.

366
00:21:21.500 --> 00:21:22.541
I can.

367
00:21:23.083 --> 00:21:24.541
Get about your business. Corporal.

368
00:21:24.625 --> 00:21:27.309
I'll be making rounds tomorrow night.
and I expect you at your station.

369
00:21:27.333 --> 00:21:28.500
Sir. Yes. sir.

370
00:21:49.833 --> 00:21:51.809
- "Hello."
- <i>Nahrvai.</i>

371
00:21:51.833 --> 00:21:52.934
Again.

372
00:21:52.958 --> 00:21:54.083
<i>Nahrvai.</i>

373
00:21:55.708 --> 00:21:56.726
"Stop."

374
00:21:56.750 --> 00:21:57.875
<i>Na is he.</i>

375
00:21:58.750 --> 00:21:59.791
<i>Naych.</i>

376
00:21:59.875 --> 00:22:00.875
It's hard.

377
00:22:01.333 --> 00:22:02.583
<i>Naych.</i>

378
00:22:02.708 --> 00:22:03.685
How's your arm?

379
00:22:03.709 --> 00:22:05.625
It's good. You're a healer.

380
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:08.351
Hey! What are you doing?

381
00:22:08.375 --> 00:22:10.166
I'm just moving your stuff.

382
00:22:10.250 --> 00:22:12.059
- Don't.
- It was in the way.

383
00:22:12.083 --> 00:22:13.166
Don't ever.

384
00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:14.833
I thought you were checking the comms.

385
00:22:21.958 --> 00:22:23.351
Hey.

386
00:22:23.375 --> 00:22:24.833
And you can dress yourself.

387
00:22:25.458 --> 00:22:26.684
Who packed these charges?

388
00:22:26.708 --> 00:22:27.875
That would be me.

389
00:22:38.625 --> 00:22:39.875
I can fit three more in here.

390
00:22:47.166 --> 00:22:48.500
Let's have a look at you.

391
00:22:54.500 --> 00:22:55.833
Make a soldier of you yet.

392
00:22:59.291 --> 00:23:01.434
So. I'll want weekly reports from Ferrix.

393
00:23:01.458 --> 00:23:04.059
And I want to keep
a tight hand on the budget.

394
00:23:04.083 --> 00:23:06.476
Now. what did I miss while I was gone?

395
00:23:06.500 --> 00:23:07.809
The Finkly Conference.

396
00:23:07.833 --> 00:23:10.083
They have agreed to move up your speech...

397
00:23:14.083 --> 00:23:15.184
<i>Hosnian Prime?</i>

398
00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:16.309
<i>It's useless.</i>

399
00:23:16.333 --> 00:23:18.434
They haven't broken.
misplaced. or mislabeled

400
00:23:18.458 --> 00:23:20.809
a single military component
in the past 12 quarters.

401
00:23:20.833 --> 00:23:23.934
Well. maybe there's. uh.
an unofficial ledger.

402
00:23:23.958 --> 00:23:26.434
I... I wouldn't trust
anything coming out of there.

403
00:23:26.458 --> 00:23:29.041
Imperial Navy is the only account
they have left at this point.

404
00:23:29.125 --> 00:23:30.934
and they'd never admit anything's wrong.

405
00:23:30.958 --> 00:23:32.059
You should go.

406
00:23:32.083 --> 00:23:33.666
I didn't realize how late it was.

407
00:23:34.916 --> 00:23:36.309
I'm staying if you are.

408
00:23:36.333 --> 00:23:38.750
I don't know what I'm doing.

409
00:23:39.583 --> 00:23:40.726
About any of it.

410
00:23:40.750 --> 00:23:42.101
Yes. you do.

411
00:23:42.125 --> 00:23:43.541
You're onto something.

412
00:23:44.416 --> 00:23:47.934
Kessel. Fondor.
targeting consoles from Jakku.

413
00:23:47.958 --> 00:23:51.309
proton warheads from Base Cay.
the Steergard Star path.

414
00:23:51.333 --> 00:23:52.625
He's right though.

415
00:23:53.666 --> 00:23:55.351
It's too spread out to be organized.

416
00:23:55.375 --> 00:23:56.791
But you don't believe that.

417
00:23:59.541 --> 00:24:01.101
I know this.

418
00:24:01.125 --> 00:24:04.625
If I was them. this is how I'd do it.

419
00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:06.750
I'd spread it out.

420
00:24:07.875 --> 00:24:10.166
Never climb the same fence twice.

421
00:24:10.833 --> 00:24:13.416
It's too random to be random.

422
00:24:17.250 --> 00:24:18.333
Two more files each?

423
00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:15.083
Stay focused. Clem.

424
00:25:18.500 --> 00:25:19.500
To the Rebellion.

425
00:25:20.750 --> 00:25:21.958
To the Rebellion.

426
00:25:54.125 --> 00:25:58.041
I needn't tell you how wrong
you were about Uncle Harlo.

427
00:25:58.125 --> 00:25:59.291
But you will.

428
00:25:59.375 --> 00:26:04.291
He said he never felt police work
was your chosen path.

429
00:26:04.375 --> 00:26:05.684
'Cause he knows me so well.

430
00:26:05.708 --> 00:26:07.166
And whose fault is that?

431
00:26:07.250 --> 00:26:08.333
Can I guess?

432
00:26:09.958 --> 00:26:13.500
Perhaps you'll study Uncle Harlo
with more energy in the future.

433
00:26:16.291 --> 00:26:18.416
What field is it
he thinks I should be pursuing?

434
00:26:18.500 --> 00:26:21.125
He said he wanted to think about it.

435
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:26.291
I struggled with how best to describe
to him the events that have led us here.

436
00:26:27.416 --> 00:26:29.875
I told him how sorry you were
about what happened.

437
00:26:30.458 --> 00:26:35.434
I stressed that it was a large enough
mistake to be deeply educational.

438
00:26:35.458 --> 00:26:36.851
Yes. I heard some of that.

439
00:26:36.875 --> 00:26:38.101
Our conversation?

440
00:26:38.125 --> 00:26:39.309
Your side of it.

441
00:26:39.333 --> 00:26:40.416
Hard to miss.

442
00:26:41.791 --> 00:26:44.583
Sadly. I wasn't able
to study Uncle Harlo's response.

443
00:26:45.208 --> 00:26:47.250
He knows how much we're counting on him.

444
00:26:53.666 --> 00:26:55.559
Stairs to the hangar?

445
00:26:55.583 --> 00:26:57.541
Four flights. four landings.

446
00:26:57.625 --> 00:26:59.125
Vault cage weak point?

447
00:26:59.958 --> 00:27:01.476
Top corners.

448
00:27:01.500 --> 00:27:03.041
Distance to load ramp?

449
00:27:03.125 --> 00:27:04.541
Twenty-eight meters.

450
00:27:04.625 --> 00:27:06.041
Emergency comm signal?

451
00:27:06.666 --> 00:27:08.041
Red-Red.

452
00:27:08.125 --> 00:27:09.102
Clear signal?

453
00:27:09.126 --> 00:27:10.434
My turn.

454
00:27:10.458 --> 00:27:11.666
Lieutenant Gorn.

455
00:27:12.750 --> 00:27:15.875
What's an Imperial lieutenant doing
getting involved with this?

456
00:27:17.250 --> 00:27:18.708
What difference does it make?

457
00:27:19.458 --> 00:27:21.125
Everyone else seems to know.

458
00:27:24.916 --> 00:27:27.666
He fell in love with a local woman
and lost a promotion.

459
00:27:28.958 --> 00:27:30.125
Then he lost the woman.

460
00:27:31.083 --> 00:27:32.916
Then he lost his taste for the Empire.

461
00:27:34.833 --> 00:27:36.625
Everyone has their own rebellion.

462
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:50.934
Is the shipment secure. sir?

463
00:27:50.958 --> 00:27:52.166
Attention!

464
00:27:56.500 --> 00:27:57.726
Sir.

465
00:27:57.750 --> 00:27:58.958
As you were.

466
00:28:00.166 --> 00:28:02.851
I prepared
a reduced schedule for tomorrow.

467
00:28:02.875 --> 00:28:06.226
- I know you were eager for that.
- It'll mean a great deal to the men.

468
00:28:06.250 --> 00:28:09.500
And now.
I see the gantry's still unpainted.

469
00:28:10.125 --> 00:28:11.476
I've spoken to them about it. sir.

470
00:28:11.500 --> 00:28:13.226
And yet it remains undone

471
00:28:13.250 --> 00:28:16.916
with an engineering officer from Coruscant
arriving today and in our business.

472
00:28:17.416 --> 00:28:20.708
Let's see if painting it tomorrow night
will make the point more clearly.

473
00:28:21.625 --> 00:28:22.625
Sir.

474
00:28:23.166 --> 00:28:24.601
May I speak plainly. sir?

475
00:28:24.625 --> 00:28:26.059
Plainly and quickly.

476
00:28:26.083 --> 00:28:27.166
Aldhani. sir.

477
00:28:27.958 --> 00:28:30.184
It's not many people's
first-choice assignment.

478
00:28:30.208 --> 00:28:32.226
The thing you hear when posted to Aldhani

479
00:28:32.250 --> 00:28:35.101
is that perhaps you'll be lucky enough
to be there for the Eye.

480
00:28:35.125 --> 00:28:37.166
The idea of being this close
and not seeing it.

481
00:28:37.250 --> 00:28:38.934
and I know we can't all be up there.

482
00:28:38.958 --> 00:28:41.291
but I fear morale might be crushed
by having anything more

483
00:28:41.375 --> 00:28:43.500
than an essential roster
down here tomorrow night.

484
00:28:46.875 --> 00:28:48.666
I want it painted the day after tomorrow.

485
00:28:48.750 --> 00:28:51.184
I'll be here midday.
and I expect to see it shine.

486
00:28:51.208 --> 00:28:52.684
- Absolutely. sir.
- Thank you. sir.

487
00:28:52.708 --> 00:28:54.791
Make sure the men know
how close they've come.

488
00:29:28.750 --> 00:29:30.166
Don't move.

489
00:29:31.083 --> 00:29:33.625
- 'Cause you know what'll happen.
- Hey. what are you doing?

490
00:29:36.333 --> 00:29:37.416
There we go.

491
00:29:38.958 --> 00:29:40.000
I knew it.

492
00:29:40.458 --> 00:29:42.708
I knew you were lying. I knew it.

493
00:29:43.375 --> 00:29:44.583
- Look.
- What is it?

494
00:29:45.333 --> 00:29:46.476
Kyber.

495
00:29:46.500 --> 00:29:47.833
Sky kyber.

496
00:29:48.625 --> 00:29:49.666
He's been hiding it.

497
00:29:49.750 --> 00:29:50.727
Skeen?

498
00:29:50.751 --> 00:29:52.916
- Sky kyber. Look at it glow.
- What's going on?

499
00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:54.101
I warned you.

500
00:29:54.125 --> 00:29:56.851
He comes here with nothin'
but the clothes on his back

501
00:29:56.875 --> 00:29:59.059
and a stone worth 30.000 credits?

502
00:29:59.083 --> 00:30:01.541
- You have a problem. you come to me.
- Here I am.

503
00:30:01.625 --> 00:30:04.559
I've topped out on questions. Vel.
I have reached my limit.

504
00:30:04.583 --> 00:30:06.184
He won't say why he's here.

505
00:30:06.208 --> 00:30:07.291
where he's from.

506
00:30:07.375 --> 00:30:10.291
He doesn't say what he believes in.
And now this?

507
00:30:10.375 --> 00:30:12.559
Who brings a treasure to a robbery?

508
00:30:12.583 --> 00:30:14.416
We don't have time for this.

509
00:30:14.500 --> 00:30:16.684
I need to know who I'm riding with.

510
00:30:16.708 --> 00:30:18.458
You know exactly who I am.

511
00:30:19.041 --> 00:30:21.184
- And you know I'll kill you for it.
- Okay.

512
00:30:21.208 --> 00:30:23.559
Okay. so. I guess we know
it's not a fake. huh?

513
00:30:23.583 --> 00:30:26.684
- It's your call.
- Let's not go too far. Clem.

514
00:30:26.708 --> 00:30:29.166
- I just want what's mine.
- Yeah. don't put me on the spot.

515
00:30:29.250 --> 00:30:30.416
Enough!

516
00:30:30.500 --> 00:30:31.833
Everyone stands down.

517
00:30:32.666 --> 00:30:33.666
Everyone!

518
00:30:33.750 --> 00:30:36.541
There's something coming!
There's a... There's a ship in the valley!

519
00:30:36.625 --> 00:30:37.666
Get your packs up.

520
00:30:37.750 --> 00:30:39.041
Move!

521
00:30:39.125 --> 00:30:40.291
Put the weapon away.

522
00:30:40.375 --> 00:30:42.666
Give him the stone.
You can kill each other later.

523
00:30:44.875 --> 00:30:46.541
You'd be right where I am.

524
00:30:48.250 --> 00:30:49.791
Tell yourself whatever you want.

525
00:30:49.875 --> 00:30:51.309
I think we're okay!

526
00:30:51.333 --> 00:30:53.333
It's heading towards the garrison!

527
00:30:54.333 --> 00:30:55.916
Get your stuff! Move!

528
00:30:58.208 --> 00:30:59.958
We'll talk when we're safe.

529
00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:09.750
I'm being paid.

530
00:31:11.666 --> 00:31:12.708
Paid to be here.

531
00:31:14.333 --> 00:31:15.476
You need to know?

532
00:31:15.500 --> 00:31:16.666
That's it.

533
00:31:19.458 --> 00:31:22.166
- What?
- Yeah. I'm here for the money.

534
00:31:23.125 --> 00:31:24.541
You can't live with that?

535
00:31:24.625 --> 00:31:25.851
I'm not worth it?

536
00:31:25.875 --> 00:31:27.625
I'll walk away and wish you luck.

537
00:31:28.416 --> 00:31:29.875
But that's what it is.

538
00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:34.291
I don't want to walk in
looking over my shoulder.

539
00:31:35.500 --> 00:31:36.541
You knew this?

540
00:31:37.750 --> 00:31:40.226
The choice was take him or call it off.

541
00:31:40.250 --> 00:31:42.500
- Call it off?
- You should've told us days ago.

542
00:31:43.166 --> 00:31:44.166
Maybe so.

543
00:31:44.250 --> 00:31:45.916
It just would've been something else.

544
00:31:47.541 --> 00:31:48.601
What's that mean?

545
00:31:48.625 --> 00:31:50.625
The day before is always hard.

546
00:31:51.500 --> 00:31:53.166
Too much time to worry.

547
00:31:53.250 --> 00:31:54.434
You think we're scared?

548
00:31:54.458 --> 00:31:55.851
I know you are.

549
00:31:55.875 --> 00:31:57.291
It's really only the money?

550
00:31:57.875 --> 00:31:59.309
To take a risk like this?

551
00:31:59.333 --> 00:32:00.434
Come on.

552
00:32:00.458 --> 00:32:02.309
Maybe you're the one that's afraid.

553
00:32:02.333 --> 00:32:03.708
Of course I'm afraid.

554
00:32:04.291 --> 00:32:07.184
But there's a difference
between fear and losing your nerve.

555
00:32:07.208 --> 00:32:08.583
You want out of this?

556
00:32:09.166 --> 00:32:10.166
Make a choice.

557
00:32:10.250 --> 00:32:12.166
Don't use me as an excuse.

558
00:32:15.916 --> 00:32:17.125
Cinta?

559
00:32:17.791 --> 00:32:18.791
No.

560
00:32:19.750 --> 00:32:20.791
She didn't tell me.

561
00:32:25.458 --> 00:32:27.666
Let's get to the camp in one piece.

562
00:32:28.291 --> 00:32:30.083
You can all chew on it there.

563
00:32:30.916 --> 00:32:31.916
All of you.

564
00:32:33.625 --> 00:32:34.625
Move.

565
00:32:52.375 --> 00:32:54.059
You saw me talking to Gar Ta feed.

566
00:32:54.083 --> 00:32:55.916
Mmm. You were busy tonight.

567
00:32:56.791 --> 00:32:58.958
He knows more about
what you're up to than I do.

568
00:32:59.833 --> 00:33:01.500
Must be embarrassing.

569
00:33:02.458 --> 00:33:05.416
When were you planning to tell me
about this new foundation?

570
00:33:06.750 --> 00:33:09.666
Well. I didn't think you'd be interested.

571
00:33:11.166 --> 00:33:12.208
Why is that?

572
00:33:13.708 --> 00:33:14.791
It's charitable.

573
00:33:18.083 --> 00:33:19.083
Hmm.

574
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:23.500
What's his name?

575
00:33:24.750 --> 00:33:25.791
Kloris.

576
00:33:27.750 --> 00:33:29.541
- Kloris?
- Sir?

577
00:33:30.291 --> 00:33:32.291
<i>Would you mind taking the Expressway?</i>

578
00:33:32.375 --> 00:33:33.416
Yes. sir.

579
00:34:02.166 --> 00:34:03.976
Looks just like your model.

580
00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:05.291
Should do.

581
00:34:05.375 --> 00:34:07.184
I've had plenty of time to study.

582
00:34:07.208 --> 00:34:09.458
and we've been
sneaking up here for months.

583
00:34:11.708 --> 00:34:13.101
We need to signal soon.

584
00:34:13.125 --> 00:34:14.833
Let's get a fire up. Let's go.

585
00:34:59.583 --> 00:35:01.458
Okay. that should do it.

586
00:35:09.458 --> 00:35:10.666
Skeen.

587
00:35:27.875 --> 00:35:30.041
She wants me to tell you about my brother.

588
00:35:32.166 --> 00:35:35.791
There's a long version.
but what matters is they killed him.

589
00:35:36.666 --> 00:35:37.750
He was a farmer.

590
00:35:38.791 --> 00:35:41.500
Imperial Prefect came in.
took his land. flooded it.

591
00:35:43.458 --> 00:35:44.625
He couldn't fight him.

592
00:35:45.958 --> 00:35:50.791
He couldn't bear it. so he went a boat
and filled his pockets with stones.

593
00:35:53.041 --> 00:35:55.416
I always hated the Empire.

594
00:35:57.458 --> 00:35:59.833
I don't really know
what to call how I feel now.

595
00:36:04.583 --> 00:36:05.750
What kind of farm?

596
00:36:07.541 --> 00:36:08.916
Trees.

597
00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:10.208
Pepper trees.

598
00:36:11.666 --> 00:36:12.916
Centuries of 'em.

599
00:36:17.791 --> 00:36:20.250
That's as close to an apology
as you're gonna get.

600
00:36:24.625 --> 00:36:25.875
It's close enough.

601
00:36:35.166 --> 00:36:36.583
Taramyn's in charge now.

602
00:36:37.541 --> 00:36:38.666
Completely in charge.

603
00:36:39.500 --> 00:36:40.958
I need to know you understand that.

604
00:36:41.541 --> 00:36:42.851
Where will you be?

605
00:36:42.875 --> 00:36:45.458
If all goes well.
we'll see you tomorrow night.

606
00:36:47.583 --> 00:36:50.208
I need to hear you tell me
you can follow the plan.

607
00:36:51.166 --> 00:36:52.916
You won't have a problem with me.

608
00:36:56.500 --> 00:36:57.666
Good luck to you.

609
00:36:59.083 --> 00:37:00.333
No farewells tonight.

610
00:37:01.083 --> 00:37:02.916
Plenty of work to do together tomorrow.

611
00:37:49.166 --> 00:37:50.750
I thought you were turning it off.

612
00:37:51.625 --> 00:37:52.791
I was just going to.

613
00:37:53.625 --> 00:37:55.309
You said that an hour ago.

614
00:37:55.333 --> 00:37:56.458
Am I keeping you up?

615
00:37:58.208 --> 00:38:00.000
There's nothing coming through tonight.

616
00:38:00.541 --> 00:38:02.875
You want to be useful.
go clean some coins.

617
00:38:09.791 --> 00:38:10.791
Happy?

618
00:38:16.166 --> 00:38:18.059
Have you checked your walk-away pack?

619
00:38:18.083 --> 00:38:20.059
- Yes.
- And the one on the Fondor?

620
00:38:20.083 --> 00:38:21.875
I don't like seeing you nervous.

621
00:38:25.041 --> 00:38:26.851
There's nothing else you can do. Luthen.

622
00:38:26.875 --> 00:38:29.351
They're either gonna be okay out there
or they're not.

623
00:38:29.375 --> 00:38:31.976
Well. that's a daring prediction.

624
00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:34.916
- Vel's the only one who traces back.
- No.

625
00:38:35.500 --> 00:38:37.059
The thief. And or.

626
00:38:37.083 --> 00:38:38.416
I wasn't careful.

627
00:38:38.500 --> 00:38:40.291
You wanted this to happen.

628
00:38:41.041 --> 00:38:42.208
This is what it took.

629
00:38:42.916 --> 00:38:44.416
It's never gonna be perfect.

630
00:38:45.541 --> 00:38:46.875
I wanted it too much.

631
00:38:49.208 --> 00:38:50.791
We have clients in the morning.

632
00:38:51.875 --> 00:38:53.208
Yeah. I'll be ready.

633
00:38:55.666 --> 00:38:57.583
It'll all be over this time tomorrow.

634
00:39:00.333 --> 00:39:01.916
Or it'll just be starting.

635
00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:05.000
Or that.

635
00:39:06.305 --> 00:40:06.605
